South Side to Blame for Incident at Mt. Kumgang Resort 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- A south Korean who came to tour Mt. Kumgang was shot to death by a servicewoman of the Korean People's Army at around 4:50 a.m. on July 11. A spokesman for the Guidance Bureau for Comprehensive Development of Scenic Spots issued a statement on Saturday in this regard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK feels regretful at this, the statement notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the cause of the incident, it occurred because the south Korean tourist trespassed on the area under the military control of the north side, going beyond the tourist zone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that the south Korean tourist intruded deep into the area under the military control of the north side all alone at dawn, going beyond the clearly marked boundary fence, even her shoes got wet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When a KPA servicewoman spotted her and ordered her to stop, she did not obey the order but began to run away. She kept running although the KPA servicewoman repeatedly shouted at her to stop, even firing blank bullets. The KPA servicewoman could not but open fire at her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The responsibility for the incident entirely rests with the south side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south side should be held responsible for the incident, make clear apology to the north side and take measures against the recurrence of the similar incident. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the south side authorities unilaterally announced that they would suspend the tour of Mt. Kumgang for the time being, a challenge to the north side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it is an intolerable insult to the north side, it will take a measure not to accept south Korean tourists until the south side makes proper apology for the recent incident and takes measures against the recurrence of such incident. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the cause of the incident is very clear and the north side has already confirmed the scene of the incident together with personnel of the Hyundai side right after its occurrence, it cannot accept the south side's proposal for inspecting the area of the north side for investigation.

Heads of Delegations to Six-Party Talks Meet 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- Talks of the heads of the delegations to the six-party talks were held in Beijing from July 10 to 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks estimated the implementation of the October 3, 2007 agreement and there reached an agreement on successfully winding it up before adopting a press release. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the press release, the DPRK agreed to make efforts to complete the disablement in parallel with the other five parties' winding up of economic compensation equivalent to a million tons of heavy oil on the principle of "action for action" by October. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was also agreed to set up a mechanism for verifying the fulfillment of each side's commitments within the framework of the six-party talks, pursuant to the September 19, 2005 joint statement aiming at the realization of the denuclearization of the whole Korean Peninsula.

Greetings to President of Montenegro 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, today sent a message of greetings to Philip Byanovic, President of the Republic of Montenegro, on the occasion of its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Expressing the belief that the relations between the two countries would favorably develop in mutual interests, Kim in the message wished the people of Montenegro welfare and prosperity.

Large Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy from King of Cambodia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihamoni, King of Cambodia, sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ribbon of the floral basket bore letters "I Have the Pleasure to Present This to HE Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, Eternal President of the DPRK. Norodom Sihamoni, King of the Kingdom of Cambodia".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Authorized by the King, the delegation of the ministry of the Royal Palace of the royal government of Cambodia headed by its Deputy Prime Minister Kong Sam Ol visited the DPRK embassy and laid the floral basket before the portraits of the President and General Secretary Kim Jong Il on July 7.

Large Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy from Great King of Cambodia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihanouk, Great King of Cambodia, sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ribbon of the floral basket bore letters "I Have the Pleasure to Present This to HE Generalissimo Kim Il Sung, Eternal President of the DPRK. Norodom Sihanouk of Cambodia".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Authorized by the Great King, the delegation of the ministry of the Royal Palace of the royal government of Cambodia headed by its Deputy Prime Minister Kong Sam Ol visited the DPRK embassy and laid the floral basket before the portraits of the President and General Secretary Kim Jong Il on July 7.

Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy from Guinean President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Lansana Conte, President of Guinea, sent a floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Conakry on July 8 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ribbon of the floral basket bore letters "I pay tribute to HE President Kim Il Sung. General Lansana Conte, President of Guinea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket was laid before the full-length painting depicting the President and General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the State Academy Beryozka Dancing Troupe of Russia Named after N.S. Nadezhdina on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 It was handed over to an official concerned by Mira Koltsova, head of the dancing troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gifts from the head of the dancing troupe and its manager were also conveyed.

Floral Baskets Laid before Portraits of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Functions of laying floral baskets before the portraits of smiling President Kim Il Sung were held at the Organization of Solidarity of the Peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America (OSPAAL) and the Kim Il Sung Economic Special School of Cuba on July 8 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were figures of the OSPAAL, the Cuban Institute of Friendship with the Peoples, Kim Il Sung Economic Special School of Cuba and the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification and Cubans and the DPRK ambassador to Cuba and staff members of his embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants laid floral baskets before the portraits of the smiling President and paid tribute to him.

DPRK Embassies Visited by Foreign Figures
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Figures from various circles including the general secretary of the Party for Unity and Progress of Guinea, the chairman of the Guinean National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, the chairman of the Guinea-Korea Friendship Association, the chairman of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Bangladesh, the chairman of the Central Executive Committee of the Bangladesh National Socialist Party, the general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist) and the secretary general of the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Committee visited the DPRK embassies in their capital cities between July 1 and 8 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They laid floral baskets and bouquets of flowers before the full-length painting depicting the President and General Secretary Kim Jong Il.

Anniversary of DPRK-China Treaty Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Xing Haiming, charge d' affaires a.i. of China here, gave a reception at the embassy on July 11 on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of the DPRK-China Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual Assistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Choe Chang Sik, minister of Public Health who is chairman of the C.C., the DPRK-China Friendship Association, Kim Thae Jong, vice department director of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea, Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chinese embassy officials were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Xing Haiming said at the reception that the treaty was signed by respected Premier Zhou Enlai and President Kim Il Sung, the great leader of the Korean people, 47 years ago. This was an event of weighty significance in the history of the Sino-DPRK relations, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent strategic policy of the Chinese party and government to steadily consolidate and develop the traditional relations of friendship between the two countries, he said, hoping that bilateral exchange and cooperation would be boosted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that this year will mark the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK, he wished that the Korean people would achieve greater success in the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude under the leadership of the WPK headed by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Chang Sik in his speech noted that General Secretary Kim Jong Il received Xi Jinping, vice-president of China, recently when the latter visited the DPRK and that the DPRK-China friendship is developing on good terms under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast stand of the WPK and the DPRK government to consolidate and develop the traditional DPRK-China friendship, he said, adding: We will as ever strive to do so, together with the Chinese comrades.

Early Fruit to Be Supplied to Citizens in Pyongyang
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Vehicles carrying early fruit for this year arrived here on Friday to be supplied to the citizens in the capital city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Fruit producers tended peach trees with care, true to the intention of General Secretary Kim Jong Il to provide fresh seasonal fruits to the people, and reaped hundreds of tons of peaches. They sent them to the capital city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arrays of trucks fully loaded with boxes of peaches were heading toward nurseries, kindergartens and commercial catering facilities in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even trains are used for their transport.

Marine Affairs in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government has paid deep attention to the marine affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Since the formation of the Integrated Coastal Management system, the environment and pollution of the seas have been regularly observed and relevant measures taken, making it possible to protect and manage the marine environments in a better way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Positive efforts for the sustainable development and utilization of marine resources have been exerted to register successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Industrialized sea-fish breeding and mariculture farms are being built to suit the ocean geographical conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Sinchang Offshore Farm and other farms have arranged kelp nurseries in the places the water of which has high transparency and where nutritious salts are abundant, with the result that they are producing a large amount of kelp. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They are steadily increasing marine resources such as sea cucumber, sea urchin and shell-fish and are preventing pollution by cultivating seaweed in scallop farms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Various systems including a marine ecological environmental observation system, alarm system for prevention of tsunami damage and red tide forecasting system have been introduced into the farms, greatly paying off. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Meanwhile, marine science and technology presentation meetings, film shows on marine expedition and development and collection of sea animals and plants have been organized in the DPRK on the occasion of the "Day of Sea" (July 12) and the "Months of Sea" (July and August) every year to widely disseminate marine scientific and technical knowledge among the working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The government is intensifying cooperation with the UNESCO and other international organizations for the development of marine resources and the marine science and technology.

Relentless Struggle against Imperialists' Aggression and War Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The imperialists' ceaseless military intervention and moves to ignite a war against the progressive countries are driving the international situation to constant uneasiness and bringing great misery, sufferings and disaster to the people. Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Aggression and war are the imperialists' mode of existence. They pave the way for the imperialists' unlimited plunder and accumulation of wealth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the imperialists' way of thinking and theory of existence that their escalation of the war of aggression against other countries would make them richer and enable them to wallow in luxury. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' greed precisely means aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The course covered by the imperialists means a history of aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The two world wars which recorded unforgettable tragedies in the human history in the past century clearly prove that imperialists are the worst enemy of mankind and the most brutal war force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists perpetrated brigandish wars of aggression against the progressive countries, socialist countries in different parts of the world by beginning with the Korean war in the 1950s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are resorting to more vicious and crafty methods to realize their brigandish ambition for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are becoming more crafty and vicious in their methods to perpetrate aggression and plunder under the changed situation and amidst the trend of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists make no scruple of perpetrating brigandish aggression and military intervention against the sovereign countries under the signboards of the "establishment of a democratic order", "defence of human rights" and "guarantee of peace".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If there be any change in the imperialists, it is not their aggressive nature but the more crafty and vicious methods of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Independence and peace do not come of themselves. They can be achieved only through a relentless struggle against the aggressor forces, concludes the article.

Massacre of Civilians by S. Korean Army and Police Ascertained
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Committee for Settling the Past History for Truth and Reconciliation on July 10 ascertained the fact that the south Korean puppet army and police massacred civilians during the last Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee pointed out that the field investigation into the massacre based on testimonies and other data proved that 457 civilians were killed in eight townships and sub-counties in Uljin, North Kyongsang Province, Haenam in South Jolla Province, Phyongthaek in Kyonggi Province and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It proved that the then puppet army and police indiscriminately killed the innocent people under the absurd charges that "they held official posts and joined some organizations in the areas liberated by the KPA, came late when the south Korean army issued the order of call, put on military shoes of the People's Army, etc." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These are the crimes against humanity, the committee said, urging the authorities to make an official apology to the bereaved families of the victims and compensate to them who have suffered pains and discrimination.

64th Candlelight Action against Beef Import Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The 64th candlelight action against the import of American beef was held in Seoul on July 10 under the sponsorship of the Citizens' Society for Protecting Candlelight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The action started when civic and public organizations including the Professors Union and the Federation of Health and Medical Organizations called a press conference in Jongro. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the press conference the organizations charged that the "government" is practicing violence against the participants in the candlelight rallies and investigating Netizens by mobilizing prosecutors to crack down upon the candlelight actions in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They urged the "government" to stop the unwarranted act of quelling the people's mind-set and opt for total renegotiations on the beef import with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The conference was followed by a candlelight rally at which speakers declared that they would continue fighting until the "government" has knelt down before the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the rally the participants held a demonstration march, valiantly fighting against the policemen hell-bent on suppressing them at the instruction of the security authorities.

Candlelight Struggle Unabated in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Those on the want list including Room Chief Pak Won Sok of the People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Markets to American Beef have been on a sit-in strike inside tents in Seoul for the last several consecutive days, according to MBC of south Korea on July 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They condemned the "government" for running wild to put down the candlelight struggle as evidenced by the search operation conducted against the office of the council and confiscation of papers and arrest of its core members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They urged the "government" to accept the people's demands and immediately opt for total renegotiations with the U.S. on beef import. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared they would carry on the candlelight meeting at Jogye Temple everyday till the people's demands are met. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to KBS of south Korea, they said the Buddhist circle of south Korea would reorganize "the Committee for Promoting the Mass on the Situation" into a permanent organization and launch positive activities.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee in a statement on July 8 said that the Buddhists would launch a 1 000-day candlelight struggle braving the crackdown by the Lee Myung Bak "government."

Release of Pro-Reunification Patriotic Youth Urged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification in a statement on July 9 strongly called for stop to the suppression of Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the headquarters, and his immediate release. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled that the 7th public trial of Yun was held at the Seoul Central District Court on July 4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the authorities of even producing a letter written by him in prison and the pocket-book which they seized from him when walking him off as evidence in a bid to bring a charge against him at any cost at the trial, the statement held that the letter and the pocket-book reflect his conscience, faith and ideology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the authorities, not content with keeping him in custody on the charge of violation of the "National Security Law", took issue with them, the statement noted, adding that this is nothing but a tyrannical action of infringing upon the freedom of thinking and conscience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no ground for the authorities to arrest and detain Yun in the June 15 era of reunification, the statement held, demanding the authorities stop suppressing the freedom of thinking and conscience and immediately set free the pro-reunification patriotic young man without any condition.

Lee Myung Bak's "Policy Speech" under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- A "policy speech" made by traitor Lee Myung Bak of south Korea at the "opening ceremony of the 18th term National Assembly" was an intolerable insult and mockery of the Korean nation and the public at home and abroad aspiring after the improved inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Traitor Lee's "policy speech" fully revealed his stance against reunification and for confrontation, it says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the speech he again raised the "theory of giving priority to the nuclear issue", saying that he would give top priority to the denuclearization of the north and the settlement of the nuclear issue of the north is an urgent task. He has become all the more desperate, blustering that he makes it clear once again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that he failed to clarify his stand on the historic June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration but glossed over them by combining them with other agreements reached between the north and the south in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traitor talked about the necessity to advance toward the "era of practice going beyond the era of declaration" and "fresh thinking and orientation." This betrays his sinister intention to overturn the historic declarations between the north and the south, nullify the successes achieved by them after the publication of the June 15 joint declaration and mislead the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traitor's talk about the "resumption of multi-faceted dialogue" proved that it was nothing but an empty talk and his confrontational "policy towards the north" remains unchanged and that he has become all the more vicious in challenging the trend of the times and desire and requirements of the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee Myung Bak had better stop clumsy rhetoric that can work on nobody but make clear his stand on the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration to all Koreans before anything else.

Struggle against American Beef Import Unabated in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- The struggle against the import of American beef is going on in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 65th candlelight rally was held in Seoul on July 11 under the co-sponsorship of the south Korean Confederation of Trade Unions and the Common Action of Men of Culture and Artistes with Candlelight of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by more than 3,000 members of trade unions, men of culture and artistes, members of civic and public organizations, school youth and children and citizens from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed a performance given by the men of culture and artistes opposing the American beef import and denouncing the suppression of the candlelight struggle by traitor Lee Myung Bak. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KCTU held "a meeting for smashing the suppression by public security authorities, opposing import of mad cattle and denouncing the Lee's regime" at the plaza of Seoul Railway Station with more than 1,000 trade union members affiliated with it attending on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers including Ri Sok Haeng, chairman of the KCTU, stressed that the KCTU together with the citizens will struggle to the last to realize the demand of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meeting the participants of the rally marched along the streets as far as Chonggye Plaza, the venue of the 65th candlelight rally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pae Sam Yong, chief of a branch of the "Central Council of the Alliance of Agricultural Organizations" under the Office Clerks Union of south Korea, staged a demonstration opposing the import of American beef and discrimination against part-time workers and the branch held a press conference in demand of the stop to the suppression of the trade unions and the discrimination against part-time workers on the same day.

S. Korean Puppet Military Authorities' Moves to Introduce Early Warning Radar under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification of south Korea called a press conference in Seoul on July 9 at which it demanded the puppet military authorities stop the moves for introducing an early warning radar for the building of the missile defense system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization disclosed the military authorities' discussion on the issue of introducing the early warning radar necessary for the MD system by 2012 at a "defence affairs promotion committee" on June 26. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that the U.S.-made radar can detect objects as far as 1,800 kms and its deployment in south Korea was the long-cherished ambition of the U.S. in its bid to build a worldwide ballistic missile monitoring network. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its realization will spur the U.S. moves to build the MD, beclouding the prospect of achieving peace on the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Northeast Asia, the organization held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the introduction of the radar will force south Korea to get embroiled in arms race, the organization called for an immediate stop to the moves for introducing the above-said radar.

Kim Il Sung Remembered in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- Meetings to remember President Kim Il Sung took place in Cambodia, Guinea and Indonesia from July 1 to 7 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deputy prime minister in charge of the Royal Palace of Cambodia said at the meeting that President Kim Il Sung was the great man and benefactor to be always remembered as he not only built the DPRK into a socialist power but supported the Cambodian people's struggle for national salvation both materially and morally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Great King Sihanouk and King Sihamoni, always telling about the President, underscored the need to boost the fraternal friendly and cooperative relations between the peoples of the two countries generation after generation, the deputy prime minister noted, adding that the Cambodian government and people would make all efforts to steadily develop the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries on good terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director general of the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea spoke of the warm care shown by the President for the foundation and development of the institute and highly appreciated the exploits performed by the President for the agricultural development in the African countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager of the Rabitra Bahtera Pratama Co. of Indonesia and other speakers stressed that the President always lives in the hearts of not only the Korean people but the world progressives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK film shows and book and photo exhibitions took place in Iran, Indonesia, India and Singapore from July 2 to 6.

Kim Il Sung's Exploits Praised in Foreign Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- The Paektusan Czech�|Korean Friendship Association issued a special information bulletin on July 6 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of demise of President Kim Il Sung and the 55th anniversary of the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article titled "Maxim of President Kim Il Sung" said that the President, believing in the people and relying on them all his life, made sure that the line and policies representing the people's desire and wishes were shaped and the popular masses' interests and convenience were given primary consideration when building any factory and city, adding that his loving care reached every nook and corner of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article titled "Exploits the President Performed by Winning a Victory in the War" stressed that the victory of the Korean people in the Korean war would be unthinkable without the rare commanding art of the President who gave full play to the political and ideological superiority of the army and people based on the unique Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of University of Kinshasa of Democratic Congo also issued a bulletin on July 4 which carried an article praising the exploits the President performed by uniting the army and people as one and thereby providing a sure guarantee for the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War.

Reception Given at DPRK Embassy in Beijing
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 12 (KCNA) -- A reception was given at the DPRK embassy in Beijing on July 10 on the occasion of the 47th anniversary of the conclusion of the DPRK-China Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual Assistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK Ambassador to China Choe Jin Su said in his speech at the reception that the peoples of the two countries have steadily boosted the friendly and cooperative relations in politics, economy, culture and other fields in the spirit of the treaty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-China friendship is a precious legacy provided by the leaders of the elder generation of the two countries and bequeathed by them to the next generation and has steadily developed on good terms under the care of the top leaders of the two counties, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is the consistent stand of the Workers' Party of Korea and the government of the DPRK to steadily boost the DPRK-China friendship, he expressed the belief that these friendly relations would continue to grow stronger thanks to the common efforts of the parties, governments and peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Qian Yunlu, vice-chairman and secretary general of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, said in his speech that the two countries have made positive contributions to promoting socialist construction and defending regional peace and stability by politically understanding and respecting each other, economically supporting and cooperating with each other in the international arena, guided by the spirit of the treaty for the past 47 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years the Sino-DPRK relations of friendship have achieved fresh steady progress thanks to the common efforts of both sides, he said, reiterating that the Chinese people together with the Korean comrades would thoroughly implement the important agreement made by the top leaders of the two countries and thus further develop them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the two countries would greet the 60th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties next year, expressing belief that the flower of Sino-Korean friendship would be brought into fuller bloom thanks to the common efforts of both sides on the above-said occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were officials of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries, the Foreign Ministry and the General Logistics Department of the Chinese People's Liberation Army and other officials concerned.

Anniversary of Demise of Kim Il Sung Commemorated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- Joint meetings to remember President Kim Il Sung were held by political parties and organizations in Bangladesh and India and meetings to remember him in Cambodia, Nepal and Switzerland between July 5 and 7 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed at the venues of the meetings were reminiscences of the President "With the Century", famous works of the peerless great men, photos showing their undying feats and books and pictures introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers including Rashed Khan Menon, chairman of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Bangladesh, highly praised the President who founded the immortal Juche idea and the Songun idea, liberated the country and led the three year-long Korean War to victory as the outstanding strategist and an invincible and iron-willed commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the President is the peerless patriot and an eternal sun of humankind as he devoted his all to the reunification of the country and the development of the world socialist movement and the Non-Aligned Movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist) and the chairman of the Nepal Institute for the Juche Studies said that the history knows no other man but the President who led the cause of the national liberation, the social revolution of several stages and the wars against the two formidable imperialisms to victory in one generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Switzerland-Korea Committee emphasized that the President is the world political elder lauded by all people as he performed immortal exploits for the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages to General Secretary Kim Jong Il were adopted at meetings held in Nepal, Switzerland and Bangladesh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, film shows took place in Germany, Syria, Malaysia and Indonesia from July 4 to 7 on the same occasion.

July 4 Joint Statement Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, July 13 (KCNA) -- The Arab Committee for Solidarity with Korean People and Supporting the Reunification of Korea headquartered in Jordan issued a statement on July 8 to support the July 4 joint statement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement noted that the publication of the July 4 joint statement 36 years ago in which the three principles of national reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and great unity of the nation--are clarified marked the first breakthrough in the frozen relations between the north and south of Korea which lasted for several decades and a historical event that materialized the slogan for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It mentioned that the three principles are the precious fruition of the wisdom and foresight of President Kim Il Sung who enjoys immortality and serve as the programme for Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that General Secretary Kim Jong Il formulated the three principles for national reunification, the ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo set forth by the President as the three charters for national reunification and inspired the Korean people to the drive to carry them out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 North-South Joint Declaration serves as the landmark for reunification of Korea which confirmed the justice of the Juche idea and the Songun idea in the new century and the October 4 declaration an action programme which can be realized by dint of the powerful might of Songun, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement expressed the full support and solidarity with the government and the people of the DPRK struggling for the independent reunification under the banner of "By our nation itself".

Kim Jong Il inspecciona la Unidad No. 895 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 11 de julio (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea inspecciono la Unidad No. 895 del EPC, laureada con el titulo del Septimo Regimiento de O Jung Hup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Luego de ver los ejercicios de los militares el Comandante Supremo se mostro satisfecho de que los uniformados de la unidad crecen como valientes soldados capaces de pelear uno contra cien enemigos realizando con vigor los ejercicios sin secar sus uniformes mojados del sudor bajo la decision de acoger con los exitos de ejercicios militares y politicos el 60 aniversario de la fundacion de la RPDC y presento las tareas que se presentan para fortalecer mas la combatividad de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Senalo que la primera tarea revolucionaria del militar es hacer bien los ejercicios y preciso que han de concentrar todas las fuerzas en el fortalecimiento del entrenamiento. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Durante el recorrido por la casa de militares, la biblioteca y otras instalaciones culturales y educativas el Dirigente se entero de los detalles del estado de realizacion de la labor politica sobre los militares  y evaluo que la unidad arreglo bien  bases culturales y educativas y realizo novedosamente la labor ideo-politica valiendose de varias formas y metodos para formar a los uniformados como heroes de nuevo siglo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Tras ver los datos de episodios hermosos de camaraderia que se ponen de pleno manifiesto entre los oficiales y soldados de la unidad, dijo que es invencible la colectividad unida por la camaraderia, la fila compactamente unida como un haz basandose en la camaraderia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Recorriendo por el recinto del cuartel rodeado del bosque frondoso hizo conocimiento del estado de la plantacion de arboles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Se mostro muy satisfecho de que  los militares de la unidad, unidos monoliticamente, realizaron magnificamente la creacion de bosques en el recinto y el contorno de cuartel y evaluo altamente sus meritos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ahora la sociedad, al aprender el modelo del ejercito, se levanto como un solo hombre en la repoblacion forestal con el extraordinario entusiasmo, agrego y enseno que todo el ejercito y todo el pueblo, movilizados, deben  hacer mas verde  la patria y convertirla en un paraiso del pueblo  hermoso y confortable para vivir. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Acto seguido, recorrio la sala de educacion, el dormitorio, el comedor, el bano, el deposito de alimentos subsidiarios y otros lugares prestando profunda atencion a la labor y la vida de los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Estuvo muy complacido de que la unidad acondiciono comodamente a la vida de los soldados las instalaciones de intendencia y evaluo sus estilos de vida esmerados y hacendosos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El Dirigente dio como recuerdo binoculos, ametralladora y fusil automatico a los militares de la unidad y se fotografio junto a estos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;         
Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC, Hyon Chol Hae y Kim Myong Guk.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona la Unidad No. 280 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 12 de julio (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono la Unidad No. 280 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Al recorrer la sala de presentacion del historial guiado por el jefe de la unidad, el Comandante Supremo evaluo altamente los orgullosos meritos realizados en el pasado por ella destacando que esta unidad incrementada y fortalecida como filas combativas capaces de pelear a solas contra cien enemigos vino manifestando sin reservas el impetu heroico del EPC en la defensa de la patria y la construccion socialista bajo la sabia direccion y atencion del partido y el Lider. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
En el aula de leccion militar averiguo como marchan los ejercicios de los oficiales de mando. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Muy satisfecho de que mediante los ejercicios sustanciales para elevar la capacidad de mando de operaciones, la unidad forma a todos los oficiales como aguerridos combatientes con alta capacidad organizativa y de mando de operaciones y combates que pueden organizar y comandar diestramente cualesquier misiones dificiles de la guerra moderna, presento las tareas para fortalecer la combatividad de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Tras cerciorarse del estado de cumplimiento de guardia y de conservacion de los medios tecnicos de combate por parte de la unidad, elogio a los oficiales y soldados que cumplen la guardia observando con aguda vigilancia cada movimiento de los enemigos y cuidan como las ninas de sus ojos las armas de la revolucion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Recorriendo la casa de los militares, la biblioteca y otras instalaciones de cultura y educacion, hizo conocimiento del estado de la labor politica a los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Se puso muy contento de que al realizar a buen ritmo la labor de educacion politico-ideologica con variados datos educativos, la unidad convierte a los militares en los fuertes en ideologia y fe con invariable conviccion y obligacion moral hacia el Partido y el Lider. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Destaco que la ideologia del Juche es la bandera combativa que el ejercito popular debe levantar en alto en todos los tiempos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Acto seguido, recorrio el dormitorio, el comedor, el bano, el deposito de alimentos subsidiarios y otras facilidades de intendencia prestando profunda atencion a la vida de los militares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Luego de disfrutar la funcion artistica de los uniformados de una compania subordinada a la unidad, el Dirigente se alegro mucho de que ellos viven de modo revolucionario llenos de optimismo y alegria y evaluo altamente sus exitos de funcion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Seguidamente, se fotografio junto con los militares de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC, Hyon Chol Hae y Kim Myong Guk.
